  "prompt": "Are there other movies like The Secret?",
  "response": "Certainly! If you found inspiration in \"The Secret,\" which delves into the Law of Attraction and the power of positive thinking, you may appreciate the following movies and documentaries that explore similar themes of personal development, spirituality, and transformative thinking:\n\n1. **What the Bleep Do We Know!?** (2004)\n   - **Genre:** Documentary, Sci-Fi\n   - **Synopsis:** This film combines documentary-style interviews, computer-animated graphics, and a narrative storyline to explore the intersections of quantum physics, consciousness, and spirituality, challenging viewers to rethink their perceptions of reality.\n\n2. **Heal** (2017)\n   - **Genre:** Documentary\n   - **Synopsis:** \"Heal\" examines the mind-body connection, featuring interviews with experts in various fields who discuss how thoughts, beliefs, and emotions can influence physical health and overall wellbeing.\n\n3. **I AM** (2010)\n   - **Genre:** Documentary\n   - **Synopsis:** Directed by Tom Shadyac, this film explores fundamental questions about the meaning of life, happiness, and human interconnectedness, featuring interviews with spiritual leaders, scientists, and philosophers.\n\n4. **The Shift** (2009)\n   - **Genre:** Documentary, Inspirational\n   - **Synopsis:** Also starring Rhonda Byrne, \"The Shift\" follows a man\u2019s journey from striving for success to seeking deeper fulfillment and purpose, highlighting the transition from ambition to meaningful living.\n\n5. **The Power of Now** (Upcoming)\n   - **Genre:** Documentary, Spiritual\n   - **Synopsis:** Based on Eckhart Tolle's best-selling book, this film delves into the importance of living in the present moment and achieving inner peace, featuring insights from the author himself.\n\n6. **The Celestine Prophecy** (2006)\n   - **Genre:** Adventure, Spiritual\n   - **Synopsis:** Adapted from James Redfield's novel, this movie explores spiritual awakenings and synchronicities that guide individuals toward their personal missions and deeper understanding of life\u2019s purpose.\n\n7. **You Can Heal Your Life** (2011)\n   - **Genre:** Documentary, Self-Help\n   - **Synopsis:** Based on Louise Hay\u2019s teachings, this film discusses how positive affirmations and self-love can lead to profound personal transformation and healing.\n\n8. **The Science of Happiness** (Various Titles)\n   - **Genre:** Documentary Series\n   - **Synopsis:** Numerous documentaries and series under this title explore scientific research behind happiness, positive psychology, and strategies to enhance well-being.\n\n9. **Peaceful Warrior** (2006)\n   - **Genre:** Drama, Inspirational\n   - **Synopsis:** Based on Dan Millman\u2019s book, the film follows a young athlete who meets a spiritual mentor, leading him on a journey of personal transformation and self-discovery.\n\n10. **The Alchemist** (Upcoming Animated Adaptation)\n    - **Genre:** Animation, Adventure, Spiritual\n    - **Synopsis:** Based on Paulo Coelho's renowned novel, this animated film explores themes of destiny, personal legend, and the universe\u2019s role in guiding individuals toward their true paths.\n\n11. **Limitless** (2011)\n    - **Genre:** Thriller, Sci-Fi\n    - **Synopsis:** While more of a narrative film, \"Limitless\" explores the potential of the human mind and how unlocking its full capabilities can lead to extraordinary achievements and personal transformation.\n\n12. **The Pursuit of Happyness** (2006)\n    - **Genre:** Biography, Drama\n    - **Synopsis:** This biographical drama tells the true story of Chris Gardner\u2019s struggle with homelessness while raising his son and pursuing a life-changing professional career, highlighting resilience and positive thinking.\n\n13. **Frequency** (2000)\n    - **Genre:** Sci-Fi, Drama\n    - **Synopsis:** Though primarily a sci-fi thriller, it touches upon themes of connection, destiny, and the profound impact of individual actions on life\u2019s outcomes.\n\n14. **Embark Studios Presents Insights** (Upcoming Series)\n    - **Genre:** Documentary Series\n    - **Synopsis:** This series features various stories and experts discussing personal growth, mental health, and the science behind positive thinking and manifestation.\n\nThese films and documentaries offer a range of perspectives on harnessing the power of the mind, achieving personal growth, and understanding the deeper connections between our thoughts, actions, and the realities we create. Whether you prefer documentary-style explorations or narrative-driven stories, there's likely something on this list that aligns with the themes presented in \"The Secret.\"",
